<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Setup</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>$7 (3:1 points at end game)</li>
                <li>1 knight</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>End of Round</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Slide and refill buildings</li>
                <li>Reset dragon</li>
                <li>Draw new tiles</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Queen</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Take Queen meeple when kingdom has acquired the most towers (including tying other players)</li>
                <li>$1 discount on construction</li>
                <li>Counts as a crown on largest territory at end game</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h3>Turn Order</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Add domino (mandatory)</li>
                <li>Add 1-2 knights
                    <ul>
                        <li>may add 1 to each square</li>
                        <li>may add to territory that already has knights</li>
                        <li>collect $X, where X = size of territory</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Construct a building
                    <ul>
                        <li>pay board cost</li>
                        <li>place it on any available construction square, red side up</li>
                        <li>collect any immediate bonuses</li>
                        <li>may not stack buildings or overbuild</li>
                        <li>do not slide tiles after building</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Bribe the dragon
                    <ul>
                        <li>only available 1x per round (if he is still in cave)</li>
                        <li>pay $1 to discard a tile and move dragon to that space</li>
                        <li>action not available to player hosting the Queen</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Select new domino (mandatory)</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>




<h3>Kingdomino and Age of Giants</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Randomize 6 AoG tiles to shuffle into Queendomino tiles; others into Kingdomino tiles</li>
    <li>Should have 54 tiles in each stack</li>
    <li>Split stacks to represent turns
        <ul>
            <li>Draw 4 tiles in half the turns</li>
            <li>Draw 5 tiles in the other half</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>In turns with 5 tiles, remove tile(s) as described in AoG</li>
    <li>4-player numbers
        <ul>
            <li>7x7 grid <span class="arrow"></span> 24 turns/dominoes per player; 12 turns from each stack</li>
            <li>Each set: 6 turns with 5 dominoes; 6 turns with 4 dominoes</li>
            <li>Each set: (6 <span class="cross"></span> 5) + (6 <span class="cross"></span> 4) = 54</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>


